parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Electronic Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine and failure of electronic systems can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the electronics on the front dash go blank
the check engine light comes on and goes off intermittently
the vehicle is unable to start for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil spring bracket can cause the front of the vehicle to jump into the air, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries. Additionally, the failure can cause damage to other components, such as the speedometer, and illuminate warning lights on the dashboard.
symptoms: The vehicle jumps into the air
and objects may fly off the vehicle. Warning lights on the dashboard may illuminate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power while driving can cause the vehicle to stall or slow down unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls while driving
the vehicle has a lack of acceleration
